member.remarks:

A call to the  method returns a D3D_SHADER_VARIABLE_TYPE value in the  Type member of a   structure. The types in a structured buffer describe the structure of the elements in the buffer. The layout of these types generally match their C++ struct counterparts. The following examples show structured buffers: 	
 struct mystruct {float4 val; uint ind;}; RWStructuredBuffer<mystruct> rwbuf;	
RWStructuredBuffer<float3> rwbuf2;


Shader code contains metadata that can be inspected using the reflection APIs. The following code illustrates retrieving a ID3D11ShaderReflection Interface from a shader. 	
 pd3dDevice->CreatePixelShader( pPixelShaderBuffer->GetBufferPointer(), pPixelShaderBuffer->GetBufferSize(), g_pPSClassLinkage, &g_pPixelShader ); ID3D11ShaderReflection* pReflector = NULL; 	
D3DReflect( pPixelShaderBuffer->GetBufferPointer(), pPixelShaderBuffer->GetBufferSize(),  IID_ID3D11ShaderReflection, (void**) &pReflector);
